    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-30T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-30T08:00:00-05:00" n="9"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/4–3049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-30T21:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 30, 1949—9 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:42 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1456. News item that British Foreign Office spokesman plans establish “friendly
                    relations” with Chinese Communist Government lends point, I believe, to mytel
                    1389, April 27, 11 a.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d9fn23">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1251">p. 1251</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
